e.', 72947, 0), (458033, 'In fact, I argue that the future of advertising, whatever the technology, will be to associate each brand with one word. This is one word equity. It''s the modern equivalent of having the best site on the high street, except the location is in the mind.', 66829, 0), (458034, 'The fox has many tricks. The hedgehog has but one. But that is the best of all.', 760, 0), (458035, 'Expect the best, plan for the worst, and prepare to be surprised.', 1391, 0), (458036, 'I like to stay happy, and I like to live life light and make the best of life.', 69256, 0), (458037, 'If I''m honest I have to tell you I still read fairy-tales and I like them best of all.', 999, 0), (458038, 'America has the best doctors, the best nurses, the best hospitals, the best medical technology, the best medical breakthrough medicines in the world. There is absolutely no reason we should not have in this country the best health care in the world.', 67591, 0), (458039, 'No hours, nor amount of labor, nor amount of money would deter me from giving the best that there was in me.', 66594, 0), (458040, 'The best executive is one who has sense enough to pick good people to do what he wants done, and self-restraint enough to keep from meddling with them while they do it.', 1674, 0), (458041, 'I did the best I could, and in some arenas, my best was not good enough. I''ve made some bad choices.', 64661, 0), (458042, 'When I was a boy, the priest, my uncle, carefully inculcated upon me this proverb, which I then learned and have ever since kept in my mind: ''Dico tibi verum, Libertas optima rerum; Nunquam servili, sub nexu vivito, fili.'' ''I tell you a truth: Liberty is the best of things, my son; never live under any slavish bond.''', 29482, 0), (458043, 'Look whether it be indifferently, as well for sins secret as open, what you find to be your best cordials to comfort you, whether God''s Word, or natural means.', 72948, 0), (458044, 'Punishment may make us obey the orders we are 