e or two really good friends, we are lucky.', 247, 0), (458463, 'My trust in God flows out of the experience of his loving me, day in and day out, whether the day is stormy or fair, whether I''m sick or in good health, whether I''m in a state of grace or disgrace. He comes to me where I live and loves me as I am.', 575, 0), (458464, 'Do your little bit of good where you are it''s those little bits of good put together that overwhelm the world.', 2109, 0), (458465, 'Win or lose, I''ll feel good about myself. That''s what is important.', 72994, 0), (458466, 'All tyranny needs to gain a foothold is for people of good conscience to remain silent.', 2026, 0), (458467, 'I define a ''good person'' as somebody who is fully conscious of their own limitations. They know their strengths, but they also know their ''shadow'' - they know their weaknesses. In other words, they understand that there is no good without bad. Good and evil are really one, but we have broken them up in our consciousness. We polarize them.', 10624, 0), (458468, 'Turn off your email; turn off your phone; disconnect from the Internet; figure out a way to set limits so you can concentrate when you need to, and disengage when you need to. Technology is a good servant but a bad master.', 3243, 0), (458469, 'Marriage is good for those who are afraid to sleep alone at night.', 62829, 0), (458470, 'Unless you have bad times, you can''t appreciate the good times.', 63097, 0), (458471, 'It turns out that advancing equal opportunity and economic empowerment is both morally right and good economics, because discrimination, poverty and ignorance restrict growth, while investments in education, infrastructure and scientific and technological research increase it, creating more good jobs and new wealth for all of us.', 17805, 0), (458472, 'Good health is not something we can buy. However, it can be an extremely valuable savings account.', 21306, 0), (458473, 'Do all the good you can, by all the means you can, in all the ways you can, in all the places you can, at all the times you can, to all the people you can, as long as ever you can.', 1728, 0), (458474, 'By all means, marry. If you get a good wife, you''ll become happy; if you get a bad one, you''ll become a philosopher.', 1595, 0), (458475, 'All I''m trying to do is survive and make good out of the dirty, nasty, unbelievable lifestyle that they gave me.', 1097, 0), (458476, 'My childhood, I wouldn''t say it was bad. It helped me grow up. I stayed out of trouble. My parents taught me what''s wrong and right, and knowing that I had a little brother following me, I had to make sure I was doing the right thing so he knows what''s right, too. I was in the house nine days out of 10. There wasn''t nothing good outside for me.', 72995, 0), (458477, 'When one has not had a good father, one must create one.', 11, 0), (458478, 'I don''t want to be too proud, but I have a good personal style.', 21402, 0), (458479, 'I think there should be a good balance between being a good student and being able to enjoy your high school life.', 69562, 0), (458480, 'The battleline between good and evil runs through the heart of every man.', 2564, 0), (458481, 'The great thing about getting older is that you become more mellow. Things aren''t as black and white, and you become much more tolerant. You can see the good in things much more easily rather than getting enraged as you used to do when you were young.', 556, 0), (458482, 'A film is never really good unless the camera is an eye in the head of a poet.', 1256, 0), (458483, 'No man is good enough to govern another man without the other''s consent.', 1012, 0), (458484, 'I think a gentleman is someone who holds the comfort of other people above their own. The instinct to do that is inside every good man, I believe. The rules about opening doors and buying dinner and all of that other ''gentleman'' stuff is a chess game, especially these days.', 12145, 0), (458485, 'I live a very joyful life, with a lot of laughter and good times.', 72996, 0), (458486, 'The more you are positive and say, ''I want to have a good life,'' the more you build that reality for yourself by creating the life that you want.', 12497, 0), (458487, 'I put a lot of pressure on myself. I think something''s not good enough, and I won''t stop until I feel like I''ve made it. I''m never satisfied.', 60269, 0), (458488, 'My idea of a good night has always been having a lovely meal and a proper conversation.', 70095, 0), (458489, 'Inspiration comes from within yourself. One has to be positive. When you''re positive, good things happen.', 72997, 0), (458490, 'Good things are associated with blue, like clear days, more than singing the blues. Just the word ''blue'' in the singular is full of optimism and positive connotation to most people.', 42107, 0), (458491, 'Nostalgia is a file that removes the rough edges from the good old days.', 5026, 0), (458492, 'It is not enough to have a good mind the main thing is to use it well.', 2272, 0), (458493, 'Doing Good is a simple and universal vision. A vision to which each and every one of us can connect and contribute to its realisation. A vision based on the belief that by doing good deeds, positive thinking and affirmative choice of words, feelings and actions, we can enhance goodness in the world.', 66578, 0), (458494, 'Treat those who are good with goodness, and also treat those who are not good with goodness. Thus goodness is attained. Be honest to those who are honest, and be also honest to those who are not honest. Thus honesty is attained.', 15, 0), (458495, 'My idea of good company is the company of clever, well-informed people who have a great deal of conversation; that is what I call good company.', 24, 0), (458496, 'A man is born alone and dies alone and he experiences the good and bad consequences of his karma alone and he goes alone to hell or the Supreme abode.', 25555, 0), (458497, 'When you take care of yourself, you''re a better person for