n order to be rated as good as a good man in the field of her earnings, she must show herself better than he. She must be more steady, or more trustworthy, or more skilled, or more cheap in order to have the same chance of employment.', 67292, 0), (458640, 'We forget just how painfully dim the world was before electricity. A candle, a good candle, provides barely a hundredth of the illumination of a single 100 watt light bulb.', 1068, 0), (458641, 'Tennis is mostly mental. Of course, you must have a lot of physical skill, but you can''t play tennis well and not be a good thinker. You win or lose the match before you even go out there.', 37889, 0), (458642, 'To me, integrity means always doing what is right and good, regardless of the immediate consequences. It means being righteous from the very depth of our soul, not only in our actions but, more importantly, in our thoughts and in our hearts.', 4294, 0), (458643, 'To be a good citizen, it''s important to be able to put yourself in other people''s shoes and see the big picture. If everything you see is rooted in your own identity, that becomes difficult or impossible.', 28712, 0), (458644, 'Manners are a sensitive awareness of the feelings of others. If you have that awareness, you have good manners, no matter what fork you use.', 31062, 0), (458645, 'Good things happen when you meet strangers.', 25711, 0), (458646, 'You can live your life angry, bitter, mad at somebody or even guilty, not letting go of your own mistakes, but you won''t receive the good things God has in store.', 3956, 0), (458647, 'What greater bliss than to look back on days spent in usefulness, in doing good to those around us.', 3921, 0), (458648, 'Leadership is hard to define and good leadership even harder. But if you can get people to follow you to the ends of the earth, you are a great leader.', 34991, 0), (458649, 'Summer means happy times and good sunshine. It means going to the beach, going to Disneyland, having fun.', 70707, 0), (458650