ee. For the First Amendment, that is not good enough. So it is really important that we protect First Amendment rights of people no matter what side of the line they are on.', 73020, 0), (458867, 'A good villain exudes charisma and power. He has principles, though; that just gives him a level of dimension. It makes him seem to be a bit unpredictable, because he''s usually deemed as some type of evil, ruthless person, and then he shows you his principles, and you don''t know what to think of it.', 73021, 0), (458868, 'The very spring and root of honesty and virtue lie in good education.', 4891, 0), (458869, 'Before every show, I have to put perfume on. I know the crowd''s not necessarily going to smell me, but when I smell good, I feel like I can dominate the room.', 68240, 0), (458870, 'My life is good because I am not passive about it. I invest in what is real. Like real people, to do real things, for the real me.', 18099, 0), (458871, 'As long as I have my faith in God, I''m good. I know everything else is going to come.', 69653, 0), (458872, 'If you want to feel good, you have to go out and do some good.', 588, 0), (458873, 'I''m still not aware that I''m good looking.', 70679, 0), (458874, 'Better do a good deed near at home than go far away to burn incense.', 1646, 0), (458875, 'Like every other good thing in this world, leisure and culture have to be paid for. Fortunately, however, it is not the leisured and the cultured who have to pay.', 1032, 0), (458876, 'What a miserable thing life is: you''re living in clover, only the clover isn''t good enough.', 1140, 0), (458877, 'It is not good to be too free. It is not good to have everything one wants.', 144, 0), (458878, 'A man has to live with himself, and he should see to it that he always has good company.', 63019, 0), (458879, 'I believe that we parents must encourage our children to become educated, so they can get into a good college that we cannot afford.', 2223, 0), (458880, 'Good copy can''t be written with tongue in cheek, written just for a living. You''ve got to believe in the product.', 17061, 0), (458881, 'We cannot make good news out of bad practice.', 14903, 0), (458882, 'Acorns were good until bread was found.', 1035, 0), (458883, 'Good thoughts bear good fruit, bad thoughts bear bad fruit.', 2970, 0), (458884, 'Laughter is the sensation of feeling good all over and showing it principally in one place.', 3355, 0), (458885, 'No news at 4:30 a.m. is good.', 59899, 0), (458886, 'Few things are harder to put up with than the annoyance of a good example.', 286, 0), (458887, 'Confidence in the goodness of another is good proof of one''s own goodness.', 663, 0), (458888, 'Only the young die good.', 22785, 0), (458889, 'I know that every good and excellent thing in the world stands moment by moment on the razor-edge of danger and must be fought for.', 744, 0), (458890, 'A good scare is worth more to a man than good advice.', 13154, 0), (458891, 'Good leaders make people feel that they''re at the very heart of things, not at the periphery.', 19589, 0), (458892, 'There has to be evil so that good can prove its purity above it.', 1471, 0), (458893, 'I know in my heart that man is good. That what is right will always eventually triumph. And there''s purpose and worth to each and every life.', 1727, 0), (458894, 'One only dies once, and if one does not die well, a good opportunity is lost and will not present itself again.', 3961, 0), (458895, 'It''s different for different people, and for a woman it''s important to look as good she wants to look. But you don''t need to do it for someone else or to impress some male out there. You do it for your own sake. You wear what makes you feel good, you put make-up and jewellery - whatever gives you self-confidence.', 2041, 0), (458896, 'All the good ideas I ever had came to me while I was milking a cow.', 73022, 0), (458897, 'Football is about joy. It''s about dribbling. I favour every idea that makes the game beautiful. Every good idea has to last.', 69850, 0), (458898, 'As long as your intentions are solid and about growth and progression and being productive and not being idle, then you''re doing good in my book.', 22945, 0), (458899, 'I''m so single. It''s funny. I''m usually a relationship girl. I love being in love and having a partner in crime. But it''s good to be your own partner in crime. God, that makes me sound like I have multiple-personality disorder.', 70688, 0), (458900, 'I have never known much good done by those who affected to trade for the public good.', 2485, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (458901, 'You can''t fake quality any more than you can fake a good meal.', 320, 0), (458902, 'Fame is only good for one thing - they will cash your check in a small town.', 262, 0), (458903, 'I have a daughter and she''s the greatest thing that ever happened to me. She gives me a good excuse to watch cartoons.', 73023, 0), (458904, 'Contemplate the good things in your life and be grateful for them.', 66575, 0), (458905, 'Protesting is good, but healing is better. We need to see America heal.', 71466, 0), (458906, 'Judgements prevent us from seeing the good that lies beyond appearances.', 21729, 0), (458907, 'Depend upon yourself. Make your judgement trustworthy by trusting it. You can develop good judgement as you do the muscles of your body - by judicious, daily exercise. To be known as a man of sound judgement will be much in your favor.', 11281, 0), (458908, 'Here is the rule to remember in the future, When anything tempts you to be bitter: not, ''This is a misfortune'' but ''To bear this worthily is good fortune.''', 267, 0), (458909, 'A heart well prepared for adversity in bad times hopes, and in good times fears for a change in fortune.', 2542, 0), (458910, 'Be yourself, fill your life with good people, and don''t get a big head. It can all be gone tomorrow.', 73024, 0), (458911, 'Some are blessed with musical ability, others with good looks. Myself, I was blessed with modesty.', 67012, 0), (458912, '''Free Fallin'' is a very good song. Maybe it would be one of my favorites if it hadn''t become this huge anthem. But I''m grateful that people like it.', 21291, 0), (458913, 'I tend to write on an acoustic guitar or the piano. I have kind of a rule: if I can''t sit down and play this and get the song over, I don''t take it to the band, because most any good song, you can sit down and deliver it with a piano or a guitar.', 21291, 0), (458914, 'I have certain things that I stand for, certain things that I believe in, and if you don''t like it and you tell me to go to hell, I think that''s your God-given right as a fan. It''s one of those deals where I''m that one guy who is outside of that realm of good guy, bad guy. I''m just me, and it elicits a response both positive and negative.', 38715, 0), (458915, 'On a good day I think I''m handsome, on an average day I''m average. I''m a man''s man so I don''t necessarily know how cute we''re supposed to be.', 58187, 0), (458916, 'The second you think that all your good fortune is a product of your virtue, you become highly judgmental, lacking empathy, totally without self-awareness, arrogant, stupid - I mean, all the stuff that our ruling class is.', 70989, 0), (458917, 'When people see your personality come out, they feel so good, like they actually know who you are.', 56473, 0), (458918, 'If everyone were a good person, it''d obviously be a better world.', 69751, 0), (458919, 'Good fellowship and friendship are lasting, rational and manly pleasures.', 65278, 0), (458920, 'It is lamentable, that to be a good patriot one must become the enemy of the rest of mankind.', 808, 0), (458921, 'Good writing is like a windowpane.', 521, 0), (458922, 'As a matter of self-preservation, a man needs good friends or ardent enemies, for the former instruct him and the latter take him to task.', 64239, 0), (458923, 'My life off the court has changed. I''m feeling good inside, so I guess it shows on the outside too.', 71281, 0), (458924, 'A man who was completely innocent, offered himself as a sacrifice for the good of others, including his enemies, and became the ransom of the world. It was a perfect act.', 32, 0), (458925, 'I look only to the good qualities of men. Not being faultless myself, I won''t presume to probe into the faults of others.', 32, 0), (458926, 'How can you be content to be in the world like tulips in a garden, to make a fine show, and be good for nothing.', 16692, 0), (458927, 'It is a good thing to learn caution from 