oble us, we are the sons of our own deeds.', 62538, 0), (458948, 'No one can be good for long if goodness is not in demand.', 1140, 0), (458949, 'What the people want is very simple - they want an America as good as its promise.', 17554, 0), (458950, 'You cannot hold on to anything good. You must be continually giving - and getting. You cannot hold on to your seed. You must sow it - and reap anew. You cannot hold on to riches. You must use them and get other riches in return.', 10101, 0);
