INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459001, 'If you want an interesting party sometime, combine cocktails and a fresh box of crayons for everyone.', 22, 0), (459002, 'I''ve had some lovely extraordinary experiences on New Year''s Eve.', 70074, 0), (459003, 'And suns grow meek, and the meek suns grow brief, and the year smiles as it draws near its death.', 70801, 0), (459004, 'A people without the knowledge of their past history, origin and culture is like a tree without roots.', 1353, 0), (459005, 'We are not makers of history. We are made by history.', 21767, 0), (459006, 'Men make history and not the other way around. In periods where there is no leadership, society stands still. Progress occurs when courageous, skillful leaders seize the opportunity to change things for the better.', 16121, 0), (459007, 'History repeats itself, first as tragedy, second as farce.', 1336, 0), (459008, 'Following the light of the sun, we left the Old World.', 70809, 0), (459009, 'More than ever before in human history, we share a common destiny. We can master it only if we face it together. And that, my friends, is why we have the United Nations.', 29992, 0), (459010, 'Those who do not remember the past are condemned to repeat it.', 2683, 0), (459011, 'Throughout history, it has been the inaction of those who could have acted; the indifference of those who should have known better; the silence of the voice of justice when it mattered most; that has made it possible for evil to triumph.', 15968, 0), (459012, 'I believe our flag is more than just cloth and ink. It is a universally recognized symbol that stands for liberty, and freedom. It is the history of our nation, and it''s marked by the blood of those who died defending it.', 66821, 0), (459013, 'I came, I saw, I conquered.', 62623, 0), (459014, 'If you are neutral in situations of injustice, you have chosen the side of the oppressor. If an elephant has its foot on the tail of a mouse and you say that you are neutral, the mouse will not appreciate your neutrality.', 2109, 0), (459015, 'The point in history at which we stand is full of promise and danger. The world will either move forward toward unity and widely shared prosperity - or it will move apart.', 2261, 0), (459016, 'History never really says goodbye. History says, ''See you later.''', 2140, 0), (459017, 'You may write me down in history with your bitter, twisted lines. You may trod me in the very dirt, but still, like dust, I''ll rise.', 74, 0), (459018, 'The history of all previous societies has been the history of class struggles.', 1336, 0), (459019, 'It takes an endless amount of history to make even a little tradition.', 561, 0), (459020, 'I never feel lonely if I''ve got a book - they''re like old friends. Even if you''re not reading them over and over again, you know they are there. And they''re part of your history. They sort of tell a story about your journey through life.', 71254, 0), (459021, 'Geography has made us neighbors. History has made us friends. Economics has made us partners, and necessity has made us allies. Those whom God has so joined together, let no man put asunder.', 1680, 0), (459022, 'We''re running the most dangerous experiment in history right now, which is to see how much carbon dioxide the atmosphere... can handle before there is an environmental catastrophe.', 10864, 0), (459023, 'The worst thing about Halloween is, of course, candy corn. It''s unbelievable to me. Candy corn is the only candy in the history of America that''s never been advertised. And there''s a reason. All of the candy corn that was ever made was made in 1911. And so, since nobody eats that stuff, every year there''s a ton of it left over.', 1870, 0), (459024, 'Neither a wise man nor a brave man lies down on the tracks of history to wait for the train of the future to run over him.', 2119, 0), (459025, 'Yesterday is history, tomorrow is a mystery, today is God''s gift, that''s why we call it the present.', 17330, 0), (459026, 'Europe was created by history. America was created by philosophy.', 1945, 0), (459027, 'Our nation is built upon a history of immigration, dating back to our first pioneers, the Pilgrims. For more than three centuries, we have welcomed generations of immigrants to our melting pot of hyphenated America: British-Americans; Italian-Americans; Irish-Americans; Jewish-Americans; Mexican-Americans; Chinese-Americans; Indian-Americans.', 73029, 0), (459028, 'History proves that the white man is a devil.', 1730, 0), (459029, 'I feel like I''m too busy writing history to read it.', 3290, 0), (459030, 'A small body of determined spirits fired by an unquenchable faith in their mission can alter the course of history.', 32, 0), (459031, 'Legend remains victorious in spite of history.', 64168, 0), (459032, 'People are trapped in history and history is trapped in them.', 67562, 0), (459033, 'Revolutions are the locomotives of history.', 1336, 0), (459034, 'There is nothing new in the world except the history you do not know.', 16121, 0), (459035, 'Anyone who knows anything of history knows that great social changes are impossible without feminine upheaval. Social progress can be measured exactly by the social position of the fair sex, the ugly ones included.', 1336, 0), (459036, 'History, despite its wrenching pain, cannot be unlived, but if faced with courage, need not be lived again.', 74, 0), (459037, 'I live off a motto that says, ''yesterday is history, tomorrow is a mystery''. I have goals and agendas. Where ever I''ll be tomorrow, that''s where I''ll be.', 69363, 0), (459038, 'It is important for all of us to appreciate where we come from and how that history has really shaped us in ways that we might not understand.', 11622, 0), (459039, 'The United Nations has a critical role to play in promoting stability, security, democracy, human rights, and economic development. The UN is as relevant today as at any time in its history, but it needs reform.', 73030, 0), (459040, 'If you look at history, innovation doesn''t come just from giving people incentives; it comes from creating environments where their ideas can connect.', 10150, 0), (459041, 'The American flag is the symbol of our freedom, national pride and history.', 69543, 0), (459042, 'The centuries-old history and culture of India, majestic architectural monuments and museums of Delhi, Agra and Mumbai have a unique attractive force.', 50689, 0), (459043, 'The very concept of objective truth is fading out of the world. Lies will pass into history.', 521, 0), (459044, 'My heart goes out to victims and survivors of the Hurricane Katrina tragedy and to their families. This disaster will go down in history books as one of the largest natural disasters in U.S. history.', 68682, 0), (459045, 'The people of Egypt are an intelligent people with a glorious history who left their mark on civilization.', 3470, 0), (459046, 'History and experience tell us that moral progress comes not in comfortable and complacent times, but out of trial and confusion.', 10283, 0), (459047, 'History has taught us over and over again that freedom is not free. When push comes to shove, the ultimate protectors of freedom and liberty are the brave men and women in our armed forces. Throughout our history, they''ve answered the call in bravery and sacrifice.', 73031, 0), (459048, 'You must pursue this investigation of Watergate even if it leads to the president. I''m innocent. You''ve got to believe I''m innocent. If you don''t, take my job.', 9695, 0), (459049, 'My countrymen: we have reached a turning point in our history. The choice is yours. Shall we venture into this brave new world, bright with possibilities, or retreat to the safety of our familiar but sterile past? I am for crossing the frontier.', 72448, 0), (459050, 'The history of liberty is a history of resistance.', 1970, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459051, 'It does not matter how much we donate it matters whether the donation is meaningful. How to define meaningful? Let society and history judge.', 73032, 0), (459052, 'Should any political party attempt to abolish social security, unemployment insurance, and eliminate labor laws and farm programs, you would not hear of that party again in our political history.', 2119, 0), (459053, 'The test of our progress is not whether we add more to the abundance of those who have much it is whether we provide enough for those who have little.', 2261, 0), (459054, 'History is not a burden on the memory but an illumination of the soul.', 63500, 0), (459055, 'Something as curious as the monarchy won''t survive unless you take account of people''s attitudes. After all, if people don''t want it, they won''t have it.', 73033, 0), (459056, 'The history of the world is none other than the progress of the consciousness of freedom.', 2787, 0), (459057, 'We have this long history of racism in this country, and as it happens, the criminal justice system has been perhaps the most prominent instrument for administering racism. But the racism doesn''t actually come from the criminal justice system.', 1309, 0), (459058, 'It is humiliating to remain with our hands folded while others write history. It matters little who wins. To make a people great it is necessary to send them to battle even if you have to kick them in the pants. That is what I shall do.', 2005, 0), (459059, 'If you read history you will find that the Christians who did most for the present world were precisely those who thought most of the next. It is since Christians have largely ceased to think of the other world that they have become so ineffective in this.', 26, 0), (459060, 'American history is longer, larger, more various, more beautiful, and more terrible than anything anyone has ever said about it.', 67562, 0), (459061, 'I was always told that I was good in mathematics, and I guess my grades and standardized test scores supported that. My worst subjects were those that generally involved a lot of reading - English and history. So, having good test scores in math and mediocre ones in reading, I was naturally advised to major in engineering in college.', 67673, 0), (459062, 'A people without a positive history is like a vehicle without an engine.', 66913, 0), (459063, 'History is a cyclic poem written by time upon the memories of man.', 165, 0), (459064, 'We are the only class in history that has been left to fight its battles alone, unaided by the ruling powers. White labor and the freed black men had their champions, but where are ours?', 3228, 0), (459065, 'The very ink with which history is written is merely fluid prejudice.', 286, 0), (459066, 'History repeats itself. So you might wanna pay attention.', 72862, 0), (459067, 'Be as a tower firmly set Shakes not its top for any blast that blows.', 849, 0), (459068, 'History shows that all protest movements rely on symbols - boycotts, strikes, sit-ins, flags, songs. Symbolic action on whatever scale - from the Montgomery Bus Boycott to wearing a simple wristband - is designed to disrupt our everyday complacency and force people to think.', 73034, 0), (459069, 'Automobiles have always been part of my life, and I''m sure they always will be. What is it about them that moves me? The sound of a great engine, the unity and uniqueness of an automobile''s engineering and coachwork, the history of the company and the car, and, of course, the sheer beauty of the thing.', 40089, 0), (459070, 'It is impossible to predict the time and progress of revolution. It is governed by its own more or less mysterious laws.', 2475, 0), (459071, 'I love history... everything is inspired by history, so that''s why I love vintage and antiques.', 72360, 0), (459072, 'They died hard, those savage men - like wounded wolves at bay. They were filthy, and they were lousy, and they stunk. And I loved them.', 2273, 0), (459073, 'Barcelona is a very old city in which you can feel the weight of history it is haunted by history. You cannot walk around it without perceiving it.', 252, 0), (459074, 'May the friends of America rejoice! May her enemies be humbled and her censors silenced at the news of her noble exertions in continuance of those principles which have placed her so high in the annals of history and among the nations of the earth.', 16972, 0), (459075, 'History suggests that capitalism is a necessary condition for political freedom. Clearly it is not a sufficient condition.', 16707, 0), (459076, 'History has demonstrated that the most notable winners usually encountered heartbreaking obstacles before they triumphed. They won because they refused to become discouraged by their defeats.', 14130, 0), (459077, 'History, in general, only informs us of what bad government is.', 1207, 0), (459078, 'In many ways, history is marked as ''before'' and ''after'' Rosa Parks. She sat down in order that we all might stand up, and the walls of segregation came down.', 23411, 0), (459079, 'Sometimes it is said that man cannot be trusted with the government of himself. Can he, then be trusted with the government of others? Or have we found angels in the form of kings to govern him? Let history answer this question.', 1207, 0), (459080, 'The dogmas of the quiet past are inadequate to the stormy present. The occasion is piled high with difficulty, and we must rise with the occasion. As our case is new, so we must think anew and act anew.', 1012, 0), (459081, 'Debate and divergence of views can only enrich our history and culture.', 66760, 0), (459082, 'History shows that there are no invincible armies.', 11422, 0), (459083, 'History has remembered the kings and warriors, because they destroyed; art has remembered the people, because they created.', 7389, 0), (459084, 'The oppressed peoples can liberate themselves only through struggle. This is a simple and clear truth confirmed by history.', 68664, 0), (459085, 'Won''t it be wonderful when black history and native American history and Jewish history and all of U.S. history is taught from one book. Just U.S. history.', 74, 0), (459086, 'When history is erased, people''s moral values are also erased.', 36994, 0), (459087, 'When it comes to discrimination, Americans pride ourselves on how far we''ve come. Racial segregation is history. Explicit sex discrimination is banned. Same-sex marriage is the law of the land. But amidst all the progress, the male-female wage gap persists, and it''s big.', 67833, 0), (459088, 'One individual can begin a movement that turns the tide of history. Martin Luther King in the civil rights movement, Mohandas Ganhi in India, Nelson Mandela in South Africa are examples of people standing up with courage and non-violence to bring about needed changes.', 1834, 0), (459089, 'What happens when good people are put into an evil place? Do they triumph or does the situation dominate their past history and morality?', 73035, 0), (459090, 'In the long history of the world, only a few generations have been granted the role of defending freedom in its hour of maximum danger. I do not shrink from this responsibility - I welcome it.', 1680, 0), (459091, 'I don''t believe in accidents. There are only encounters in history. There are no accidents.', 981, 0), (459092, 'Among the many misdeeds of the British rule in India, history will look upon the act depriving a whole nation of arms as the blackest.', 32, 0), (459093, 'So that the record of history is absolutely crystal clear. That there is no alternative way, so far discovered, of improving the lot of the ordinary people that can hold a candle to the productive activities that are unleashed by a free enterprise system.', 16707, 0), (459094, 'The people, and the people alone, are the motive force in the making of world history.', 15795, 0), (459095, 'My only advice is, follow your dream and do whatever you like to do the most. I chose journalism because I wanted to be in the places where history was being made.', 16620, 0), (459096, 'The monuments of the nations are all protests against nothingness after death so are statues and inscriptions so is history.', 10967, 0), (459097, 'We just feel like history repeats itself. You ain''t never going to see nothing brand new you''re only going to see when records are broken. And we''re here to just set records and set trends and follow the footsteps that have been shown to us.', 72862, 0), (459098, 'History is, strictly speaking, the study of questions; the study of answers belongs to anthropology and sociology.', 219, 0), (459099, 'Junk stands and antique markets are the perfect place to pick up clues about the history of a country, region or town.', 73036, 0), (459100, 'I cannot lead you into battle. I do not give you laws or administer justice but I can do something else - I can give my heart and my devotion to these old islands and to all the peoples of our brotherhood of nations.', 65677, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459101, 'As an immigrant, I appreciate, far more than the average American, the liberties we have in this country. Silence is a big enemy of morality. I don''t want our blunders in history to get repeated.', 64979, 0), (459102, 'Who has fully realized that history is not contained in thick books but lives in our very blood?', 28934, 0), (459103, 'History is replete with ideologies of freedom, justice, liberation of the downtrodden and the exploited, that have been turned against the very people they had mobilised, or that have reproduced the same logic of exclusion and terror toward those whom they claimed to set free.', 4710, 0), (459104, 'All history has been a history of class struggles between dominated classes at various stages of social development.', 18097, 0), (459105, 'Malaysia is a country unlike any other: Full of promise and fragility. Its history, cultural and religious diversity make it a rich, compelling and surprising land.', 4710, 0), (459106, 'Condemn me. It does not matter. History will absolve me.', 3470, 0), (459107, 'I want history to remember me... not as the first black woman to have made a bid for the presidency of the United States, but as a black woman who lived in the 20th century and who dared to be herself. I want to be remembered as a catalyst for change in America.', 28343, 0), (459108, 'Study history, study history. In history lies all the secrets of statecraft.', 3621, 0), (459109, 'The more you know of your history, the more liberated you are.', 74, 0), (459110, 'Solidarity was the movement that turned the direction of history, I think.', 3797, 0), (459111, 'The main thing is to make history, not to write it.', 4746, 0), (459112, 'It all happened so fast. The ghetto. The deportation. The sealed cattle car. The fiery altar upon which the history of our people and the future of mankind were meant to be sacrificed.', 10, 0), (459113, 'We have the power to make this the best generation of mankind in the history of the world or to make it the last.', 1680, 0), (459114, 'China''s history is marked by thousands of years of world-changing innovations: from the compass and gunpowder to acupuncture and the printing press. No one should be surprised that China has re-emerged as an economic superpower.', 67139, 0), (459115, 'We would like to live as we once lived, but history will not permit it.', 1680, 0), (459116, 'History is indeed little more than the register of the crimes, follies, and misfortunes of mankind.', 7427, 0), (459117, 'Perhaps in time the so-called Dark Ages will be thought of as including our own.', 68283, 0), (459118, 'I come into the peace of wild things who do not tax their lives with forethought of grief... For a time I rest in the grace of the world, and am free.', 1152, 0), (459119, 'Hubert Humphrey talks so fast that listening to him is like trying to read Playboy magazine with your wife turning the pages.', 64083, 0), (459120, 'Peace, plenty, and contentment reign throughout our borders, and our beloved country presents a sublime moral spectacle to the world.', 71937, 0), (459121, 'History is a people''s memory, and without a memory, man is demoted to the lower animals.', 1730, 0), (459122, 'It is the greatest scam in history. I am amazed, appalled and highly offended by it. Global Warming; It is a scam. Some dastardly scientists with environmental and political motives manipulated long term scientific data to create an illusion of rapid global warming.', 70904, 0), (459123, 'In Thailand''s history there have been dissensions from time to time, but in general, unity has prevailed.', 67338, 0), (459124, 'Social media has taken over in America to such an extreme that to get my own kids to look back a week in their history is a miracle, let alone 100 years.', 5194, 0), (459125, 'Manchester United are not just some club. To be part of this club also means to be part of a great history.', 68274, 0), (459126, 'My reading of history convinces me that most bad government has grown out of too much government.', 73037, 0), (459127, 'If a race has no history, if it has no worthwhile tradition, it becomes a negligible factor in the thought of the world, and it stands in danger of being exterminated.', 3302, 0), (459128, 'I''m playing dark history. It''s beyond black. I''m dealing with the dark things of the cosmos.', 42348, 0), (459129, 'This is the lesson that history teaches: repetition.', 1267, 0), (459130, 'I am trying to make art that relates to the deepest and most mythic concerns of human kind and I believe that, at this moment of history, feminism is humanism.', 69869, 0), (459131, 'There''s probably more history now preserved underwater than in all the museums of the world combined. And there''s no law governing that history. It''s finders keepers.', 73038, 0), (459132, 'After the Berlin Wall came down I visited that city and I will never forget it. The abandoned checkpoints. The sense of excitement about the future. The knowledge that a great continent was coming together. Healing those wounds of our history is the central story of the European Union.', 28607, 0), (459133, 'A drop of water, if it could write out its own history, would explain the universe to us.', 7253, 0), (459134, 'Your genome knows much more about your medical history than you do.', 49863, 0), (459135, 'That men do not learn very much from the lessons of history is the most important of all the lessons of history.', 1032, 0), (459136, 'The megalomaniac differs from the narcissist by the fact that he wishes to be powerful rather than charming, and seeks to be feared rather than loved. To this type belong many lunatics and most of the great men of history.', 95, 0), (459137, 'That human behavior is more influenced by things outside of us than inside. The ''situation'' is the external environment. The inner environment is genes, moral history, religious training.', 73035, 0), (459138, 'The genius of vinyl is that it allows - commands! - us to put our fingerprints all over that history: to blend and chop and reconfigure it, mock and muse upon it, backspin and skip through it.', 50328, 0), (459139, 'Visual surprise is natural in the Caribbean; it comes with the landscape, and faced with its beauty, the sigh of History dissolves.', 5030, 0), (459140, 'During the long process of history, by relying on our own diligence, courage and wisdom, Chinese people have opened up a good and beautiful home where all ethnic groups live in harmony and fostered an excellent culture that never fades.', 67393, 0), (459141, 'There was no United States before slavery. I am sure somebody can make some sort of argument about modern French identity and slavery and North Africa, but there simply is no American history before black people.', 1309, 0), (459142, 'The arc of American history almost inevitably moves toward freedom. Whether it''s Lincoln and the Emancipation Proclamation, the expansion of women''s rights or, now, gay rights, I think there is an almost-inevitable march toward greater civil liberties.', 66869, 0), (459143, 'Much of the social history of the Western world, over the past three decades, has been a history of replacing what worked with what sounded good.', 2589, 0), (459144, 'Governments have never learned anything from history, or acted on principles deducted from it.', 2787, 0), (459145, 'The people who have impacted the world didn''t live long. Martin Luther King. John F. Kennedy. These people who impact the world were not old people, but they lived so effectively that we cannot erase them from history.', 11162, 0), (459146, 'If one tries to think about history, it seems to me - it''s like looking at a range of mountains. And the first time you see them, they look one way. But then time changes, the pattern of light shifts. Maybe you''ve moved slightly, your perspective has changed. The mountains are the same, but they look very different.', 2373, 0), (459147, 'Whenever I think of my birthplace, Walton-on-Thames, my reference first and foremost is the river. I love the smell of the river; love its history, its gentleness. I was aware of its presence from my earliest years. Its majesty centered me, calmed me, was a solace to a certain extent.', 62854, 0), (459148, 'The suicide bombers who struck London on 7 July 2005 killed 52 innocent people and wounded hundreds more. All of them must live with their memories. And the rest of us will always remember where we were when we heard that London had been hit by the worst terrorist attack in its history.', 67255, 0), (459149, 'I''m turned on by guys who are cultured. That''ll keep me intrigued. They don''t have to have a single degree, but they should speak other languages or know things about other parts of the world or history or certain artists or musicians. I like to be taught. I like to sit on that side of the table.', 7387, 0), (459150, 'What you see is that the most outstanding feature of life''s history is a constant domination by bacteria.', 1195, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459151, 'The haunting of history is ever present in Barcelona. I see cities as organisms, as living creatures. To me, Madrid is a man and Barcelona is a woman. And it''s a woman who''s extremely vain.', 252, 0), (459152, 'I stated that Hiroshima and Nagasaki are ''among the most unspeakable crimes in history.'' I took no position on just where they stand on the scale of horrors relative to Auschwitz, the bombing of Chungking, Lidice, and so on.', 1955, 0), (459153, 'A world without nuclear weapons would be less stable and more dangerous for all of us.', 1945, 0), (459154, 'Tell the FBI that the kidnappers should pick out a judge that Nixon wants back.', 3784, 0), (459155, 'The revolutionary breakthrough will come with rockets that are fully and rapidly reusable. We will never conquer Mars unless we do that. It''ll be too expensive. The American colonies would never have been pioneered if the ships that crossed the ocean hadn''t been reusable.', 10864, 0), (459156, 'History does not record in its annals any lasting domination exercised by one people over another, of different race, of diverse usages and customs, of opposite and divergent ideals. One of the two had to yield and succumb.', 3961, 0), (459157, 'Museums are managers of consciousness. They give us an interpretation of history, of how to view the world and locate ourselves in it. They are, if you want to put it in positive terms, great educational institutions. If you want to put it in negative terms, they are propaganda machines.', 73039, 0), (459158, 'Physics has a history of synthesizing many phenomena into a few theories.', 66888, 0), (459159, 'Blood alone moves the wheels of history.', 1746, 0), (459160, 'History repeats itself, and that''s one of the things that''s wrong with history.', 2052, 0), (459161, 'Understanding the long, sordid history of gun control in America is key to understanding the dangers of disarming.', 73040, 0), (459162, 'Crafts make us feel rooted, give us a sense of belonging and connect us with our history. Our ancestors used to create these crafts out of necessity, and now we do them for fun, to make money and to express ourselves.', 3591, 0), (459163, 'Civil disobedience has an honourable history, and when the urgency and moral clarity cross a certain threshold, then I think that civil disobedience is quite understandable, and it has a role to play.', 13473, 0), (459164, 'Classes struggle, some classes triumph, others are eliminated. Such is history; such is the history of civilization for thousands of years.', 15795, 0), (459165, 'Anyone who believes you can''t change history has never tried to write his memoirs.', 44204, 0), (459166, 'So when I read this story, it unlocked a volcano of unanswered questions, because the questions had never been asked. It was an opportunity to come to terms with the lot of repressed history - and history of repression.', 66999, 0), (459167, 'It is in Rousseau''s writing above all that history begins to turn from upper-class honour to middle-class humanitarianism. Pity, sympathy and compassion lie at the centre of his moral vision. Values associated with the feminine begin to infiltrate social existence as a whole, rather than being confined to the domestic sphere.', 1914, 0), (459168, 'My favourite finds are often antique pieces with a history.', 73041, 0), (459169, 'The injustices endured by black Americans at the hands of their own government have no parallel in our history, not only during the period of slavery but also in the Jim Crow era that followed.', 73042, 0), (459170, 'Even the most meticulous historians work subjectively. The historian''s point of view, his or her selection of subject and sources, the emphasis, the tone - all of these lead to subjective history, inevitably so. I do not say this as a criticism, merely as an observation.', 10670, 0), (459171, 'If you read enough biography and history, you learn how people have dealt successfully or unsuccessfully with similar situations or patterns in the past. It doesn''t give you a template of answers, but it does help you refine the questions you have to ask yourself.', 38429, 0), (459172, 'Read no history: nothing but biography, for that is life without theory.', 1827, 0), (459173, 'Man is not logical and his intellectual history is a record of mental reserves and compromises. He hangs on to what he can in his old beliefs even when he is compelled to surrender their logical basis.', 2575, 0), (459174, 'All the lessons of history in four sentences: Whom the gods would destroy, they first make mad with power. The mills of God grind slowly, but they grind exceedingly small. The bee fertilizes the flower it robs. When it is dark enough, you can see the stars.', 28619, 0), (459175, 'For most of history, Anonymous was a woman.', 113, 0), (459176, 'It is like writing history with lightning and my only regret is that it is all so terribly true.', 1970, 0), (459177, 'There is no history of mankind, there are only many histories of all kinds of aspects of human life. And one of these is the history of political power. This is elevated into the history of the world.', 20892, 0), (459178, 'Revolutions are the periods of history when individuals count most.', 2370, 0), (459179, 'And remember, where you have a concentration of power in a few hands, all too frequently men with the mentality of gangsters get control. History has proven that.', 63500, 0), (459180, 'This is our history - from the Transcontinental Railroad to the Hoover Dam, to the dredging of our ports and building of our most historic bridges - our American ancestors prioritized growth and investment in our nation''s infrastructure.', 10615, 0), (459181, 'Life moves fast. As much as you can learn from your history, you have to move forward.', 18483, 0), (459182, 'We don''t see the global citizen as someone with no identity, but rather someone who has confidence and is proud of his culture and history - and... open to the modern world.', 68230, 0), (459183, 'History is more or less bunk.', 1796, 0), (459184, 'The worst pandemic in modern history was the Spanish flu of 1918, which killed tens of millions of people. Today, with how interconnected the world is, it would spread faster.', 1133, 0), (459185, 'Our landscapes connect us to our history; they are the source of our character as a peopl, as well as our health, our safety, and our prosperity. Natural resources enrich us economically, yes. But they also enrich us aesthetically and recreationally and culturally and spiritually.', 60667, 0), (459186, 'No cause is left but the most ancient of all, the one, in fact, that from the beginning of our history has determined the very existence of politics, the cause of freedom versus tyranny.', 2694, 0), (459187, 'All I know is that history repeats itself and people are going to want to experience the world. But I know then they are going to have a better appreciation for what is here in Maine.', 72417, 0), (459188, 'The Communist regime didn''t consider this to be a shining moment in history and assigned no heroism to it. They classified it as merely an accident.', 66653, 0), (459189, 'The Jews'' greatest contribution to history is dissatisfaction! We''re a nation born to be discontented. Whatever exists we believe can be changed for the better.', 4770, 0), (459190, 'The more bombers, the less room for doves of peace.', 17473, 0), (459191, 'No great man lives in vain. The history of the world is but the biography of great men.', 3061, 0), (459192, 'The view of Jerusalem is the history of the world; it is more, it is the history of earth and of heaven.', 1827, 0), (459193, 'We are born, we live, we disappear. One of the chilling aspects of history is the swiftness with which it carries us into oblivion.', 10670, 0), (459194, 'Thanks to television, for the first time the young are seeing history made before it is censored by their elders.', 992, 0), (459195, 'If history could teach us anything, it would be that private property is inextricably linked with civilization.', 9998, 0), (459196, 'Tokyo may have more money and Kyoto more culture Nara may have more history and Kobe more style. But Osaka has the biggest heart.', 35806, 0), (459197, 'Americans love to fight. All real Americans love the sting of battle.', 57896, 0), (459198, 'The worst mistake of first contact, made throughout history by individuals on both sides of every new encounter, has been the unfortunate habit of making assumptions. It often proved fatal.', 1575, 0), (459199, 'History is the sum total of things that could have been avoided.', 62427, 0), (459200, 'If we could read the secret history of our enemies we should find in each man''s life sorrow and suffering enough to disarm all hostility.', 147, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459201, 'There are people in every time and every land who want to stop history in its tracks. They fear the future, mistrust the present, and invoke the security of a comfortable past which, in fact, never existed.', 60667, 0), (459202, 'Contrary to what we learn from progressives in education and the media, the history of the Democratic Party well into the twentieth century is a virtually uninterrupted history of thievery, corruption, and bigotry.', 10552, 0), (459203, 'Dorothy is the only woman in history who has had her menopause in public and made it pay.', 2203, 0), (459204, 'Human history in essence is the history of ideas.', 3173, 0), (459205, 'To this wonderful page in our country''s history another more glorious still will be added, and the slave shall show at last to his free brothers a sharpened sword forged from the links of his fetters.', 63267, 0), (459206, 'Human blunders usually do more to shape history than human wickedness.', 20910, 0), (459207, 'I think documentaries are the greatest way to educate an entire generation that doesn''t often look back to learn anything about the history that provided a safe haven for so many of us today.', 5194, 0), (459208, 'All cultures through all time have constantly been engaged in a dance with new possibilities for life. Change is the one constant in human history.', 11280, 0), (459209, 'Worshipping the Lord means giving Him the place that he must have; worshipping the Lord means stating, believing - not only by our words - that He alone truly guides our lives; worshipping the Lord means that we are convinced before Him that He is the only God, the God of our lives, the God of our history.', 6248, 0), (459210, 'The acceptance of the facts of African-American history and the African-American historian as a legitimate part of the academic community did not come easily. Slavery ended and left its false images of black people intact.', 50699, 0), (459211, 'God will use whatever he wants to display his glory. Heavens and stars. History and nations. People and problems.', 86, 0), (459212, 'Of the twenty-two civilizations that have appeared in history, nineteen of them collapsed when they reached the moral state the United States is in now.', 63443, 0), (459213, 'Here you have an incredibly ambitious, accomplished woman who comes up against some of the same problems that women in power come up against today. Cleopatra plays an oddly pivotal role in world history as well; in her lifetime, Alexandria is the center of the universe, Rome is still a backwater.', 16531, 0), (459214, 'History is a vision of God''s creation on the move.', 63443, 0), (459215, 'I was France.', 11599, 0), (459216, 'I have tried to lift France out of the mud. But she will return to her errors and vomitings. I cannot prevent the French from being French.', 11599, 0), (459217, 'The whole course of human history may depend on a change of heart in one solitary and even humble individual - for it is in the solitary mind and soul of the individual that the battle between good and evil is waged and ultimately won or lost.', 624, 0), (459218, 'Dad, I''m in some trouble. There''s been an accident and you''re going to hear all sorts of things about me from now on. Terrible things.', 73043, 0), (459219, 'History is a pack of lies about events that never happened told by people who weren''t there.', 2683, 0), (459220, 'The past is really almost as much a work of the imagination as the future.', 3164, 0), (459221, 'History never looks like history when you are living through it.', 11471, 0), (459222, 'What is history but a fable agreed upon?', 1702, 0), (459223, 'Keeping books on social aid is capitalistic nonsense. I just use the money for the poor. I can''t stop to count it.', 71187, 0), (459224, 'If we celebrate Martin Luther King Jr.''s birthday at a time of presidential inaugurals, this is thanks to Ronald Reagan who created the holiday, and not to the Democratic Congress of the Carter years, which rejected it.', 71537, 0), (459225, 'All of us have a place in history. Mine is clouds.', 1262, 0), (459226, 'What has history said of eminence without honor, wealth without wisdom, power and possessions without principle? The answer is reiterated in the overthrow of the mightiest empires of ancient times. Babylon, Persia, Greece, Rome! The four successive, universal powers of the past. What and where are they?', 9105, 0), (459227, 'Jewelry and pins have been worn throughout history as symbols of power, sending messages. Interestingly enough, it was mostly men who wore the jewelry in various times, and obviously crowns were part of signals that were being sent throughout history by people of rank.', 17868, 0), (459228, 'History is so subjective. The teller of it determines it.', 1844, 0), (459229, 'I don''t want a Black History Month. Black history is American history.', 30247, 0), (459230, 'Racism is an ism to which everyone in the world today is exposed; for or against, we must take sides. And the history of the future will differ according to the decision which we make.', 9314, 0), (459231, 'I''m a child of immigrants. That is the history of this country. Immigration is good and important for our country. Legal immigration needs to really be modernized.', 73044, 0), (459232, 'My lifestyle is a consequence of my wounds. I''m the son of my history.', 67901, 0), (459233, 'Jesus Christ belonged to the true race of prophets. He saw with open eye the mystery of the soul. Drawn by its severe harmony, ravished with its beauty, he lived in it and had his being there. Alone in all history, he estimated the greatness of man.', 760, 0), (459234, 'There are great legends and great fighters in the history of Mexico, and there will be more to come.', 69308, 0), (459235, 'There comes a time in the life of every nation when it stands at the crossroads of history and must choose which way to go.', 67654, 0), (459236, 'There has never yet been a man in our history who led a life of ease whose name is worth remembering.', 1674, 0), (459237, 'The greatest honor history can bestow is that of peacemaker.', 9695, 0), (459238, 'Uncertainty and fear and ignorance about immigrants, about people who are different, has a history as old as our Nation.', 67343, 0), (459239, 'History does nothing; it does not possess immense riches, it does not fight battles. It is men, real, living, who do all this.', 1336, 0), (459240, 'What you end up seeing when you look at history is that people who have been good at pushing the boundaries of possibility, and exploring those frontiers of good ideas and innovations, have rarely done it in moments of great inspiration. They don''t just have a brilliant breakthrough idea out of nowhere and leap ahead of everyone else.', 10150, 0), (459241, 'Considering our history, I can think of nothing more American than an immigrant.', 69022, 0), (459242, 'Every single immigrant is part of a larger history that needs to be communicated in all its ambivalences and complexities.', 72981, 0), (459243, 'If history starts as a guest list, it has a tendency to end like the memory of a drunken party: misheard, blurred, fragmentary.', 73045, 0), (459244, 'The history of all countries shows that the working class exclusively by its own effort is able to develop only trade-union consciousness.', 2475, 0), (459245, 'A lawyer without history or literature is a mechanic, a mere working mason; if he possesses some knowledge of these, he may venture to call himself an architect.', 972, 0), (459246, 'I still love the whole history of jazz. The old things sound better than ever.', 70833, 0), (459247, 'I pass over the toil and suffering and danger which attended the redemption and cultivation of their lands by the colonists, and turn to their civil condition and to the conduct and history of the government.', 73046, 0), (459248, 'Through all of history mankind has ingested psychedelic substances. Those substances exist to put you in touch with spirits beyond yourself, with the creator, with the creative impulse of the planet.', 68022, 0), (459249, 'History is mostly guessing the rest is prejudice.', 1167, 0), (459250, 'My place in history will depend on what I can do for the people and not on what the people can do for me.', 17514, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459251, 'People didn''t vote left or right in the election. They voted for putting an end to all the primitive political history.', 73047, 0), (459252, 'I think if you come from a history of persecution you have to develop a sense of humour.', 11926, 0), (459253, 'In the 2000 presidential election, Al Gore got more votes than George W. Bush, but still lost the election. The Supreme Court''s ruling in Florida gave Bush that pivotal state, and doomed Gore to lose the Electoral College. That odd scenario - where the candidate with the most votes loses - has happened three times in U.S. history.', 68674, 0), (459254, 'The invention of the printing press was one of the most important events in human history.', 6332, 0), (459255, 'If a strong government finds that it can, with impunity, destroy a weak people, then the hour has struck for that weak people to appeal to the League of Nations to give its judgment in all freedom. God and history will remember your judgment.', 15968, 0), (459256, 'For a privileged minority, Western democracy provides the leisure, the facilities, and the training to seek the truth lying hidden behind the veil of distortion and misrepresentation, ideology and class interest, through which the events of current history are presented to us.', 1955, 0), (459257, 'Jesus was not born in a manger in central Pennsylvania. He was a man of color. And the fact that we have represented him for centuries literally as a white man speaks to the entire history of white supremacy.', 24606, 0), (459258, 'My grandfather was Jacques Cousteau, a pioneer of ocean exploration and the co-inventor of scuba diving. Back in the 1940s when he tested out his invention which allowed humans to swim freely in the ocean with a portable air source for the first time in history, very little of the ocean had been explored let alone captured on film.', 70918, 0), (459259, 'Hegel was right when he said that we learn from history that man can never learn anything from history.', 266, 0), (459260, 'The 4th Amendment and the personal rights it secures have a long history. At the very core stands the right of a man to retreat into his own home and there be free from unreasonable governmental intrusion.', 73048, 0), (459261, 'The very concept of history implies the scholar and the reader. Without a generation of civilized people to study history, to preserve its records, to absorb its lessons and relate them to its own problems, history, too, would lose its meaning.', 3368, 0), (459262, 'History is a guide to navigation in perilous times. History is who we are and why we are the way we are.', 1315, 0), (459263, 'The public history of modern art is the story of conventional people not knowing what they are dealing with.', 12971, 0), (459264, 'Neither current events nor history show that the majority rule, or ever did rule.', 16075, 0), (459265, 'Love is the whole history of a woman''s life, it is but an episode in a man''s.', 62704, 0), (459266, 'I often say of George Washington that he was one of the few in the whole history of the world who was not carried away by power.', 35, 0), (459267, 'Our ignorance of history causes us to slander our own times.', 647, 0), (459268, 'To correct a natural indifference I was placed half-way between misery and the sun. Misery kept me from believing that all was well under the sun, and the sun taught me that history wasn''t everything.', 532, 0), (459269, 'History repeats itself, but the special call of an art which has passed away is never reproduced. It is as utterly gone out of the world as the song of a destroyed wild bird.', 1241, 0), (459270, 'Memoirs are the backstairs of history.', 18119, 0), (459271, 'The history of the world shows that peoples and societies do not have to pass through a fixed series of stages in the course of development.', 5358, 0), (459272, 'Gardeners instinctively know that flowers and plants are a continuum and that the wheel of garden history will always be coming full circle.', 73049, 0), (459273, 'The current state of knowledge is a moment in history, changing just as rapidly as the state of knowledge in the past has ever changed and, in many instances, more rapidly.', 9651, 0), (459274, 'The institution of chivalry forms one of the most remarkable features in the history of the Middle Ages.', 73050, 0), (459275, 'It''s a major part of world history that men are trying to kill each other. It''s just one slaughter after the other. We talk about it, but no one''s really listening.', 73051, 0), (459276, 'This empire, unlike any other in the history of the world, has been built primarily through economic manipulation, through cheating, through fraud, through seducing people into our way of life, through the economic hit men. I was very much a part of that.', 21156, 0), (459277, 'In known history, nobody has had such capacity for altering the universe than the people of the United States of America. And nobody has gone about it in such an aggressive way.', 45466, 0), (459278, 'We are still living in the aftershock of Hiroshima, people are still the scars of history.', 19972, 0), (459279, 'While we are living in the present, we must celebrate life every day, knowing that we are becoming history with every work, every action, every deed.', 22029, 0), (459280, 'I feel, as never before, how justly, from the dawn of history to the present time, men have paid the homage of their gratitude and admiration to the memory of those who nobly sacrifice their lives, that their fellow-men may live in safety and in honor.', 73052, 0), (459281, 'It''s a struggle but that''s why we exist, so that another generation of Lesbians of color will not have to invent themselves, or their history, all over again.', 897, 0), (459282, 'Was it not enough punishment and suffering in history that we were uprooted and made helpless slaves not only in new colonial outposts but also domestically.', 32803, 0), (459283, 'A Conservative is a fellow who is standing athwart history yelling ''Stop!''', 64070, 0), (459284, 'All History is current; all injustice continues on some level, somewhere in the world.', 753, 0), (459285, 'Do you seriously expect me to be the first Prince of Wales in history not to have a mistress?', 73033, 0), (459286, 'The history of thought may be summed up in these words: it is absurd by what it seeks and great by what it finds.', 3087, 0), (459287, 'It is possible to read the history of this country as one long struggle to extend the liberties established in our Constitution to everyone in America.', 2253, 0), (459288, 'Man watches his history on the screen with apathy and an occasional passing flicker of horror or indignation.', 73053, 0), (459289, 'History should be written as philosophy.', 808, 0), (459290, 'World history is a court of judgment.', 2787, 0), (459291, 'Newspapers are the second hand of history. This hand, however, is usually not only of inferior metal to the other hands, it also seldom works properly.', 1304, 0), (459292, 'It is not history which uses men as a means of achieving - as if it were an individual person - its own ends. History is nothing but the activity of men in pursuit of their ends.', 1336, 0), (459293, 'Madam President, speaking here in Dublin Castle it is impossible to ignore the weight of history, as it was yesterday when you and I laid wreaths at the Garden of Remembrance.', 65677, 0), (459294, 'I''m a good son, a good father, a good husband - I''ve been married to the same woman for 30 years. I''m a good friend. I finished college, I have my education, I donate money anonymously. So when people criticize the kind of characters that I play on screen, I go, ''You know, that''s part of history.''', 73054, 0), (459295, 'The ''80s were fabulous. The ''90s sucked, and the ''70s were just a sad, sad time in human history. Go 1980s! There''s something that''s just so cute about that time. And not just yellow nail polish and ''I''m a loner.''', 67271, 0), (459296, 'Culinary tradition is not always based on fact. Sometimes it''s based on history, on habits that come out of a time when kitchens were fueled by charcoal.', 32294, 0), (459297, 'We wonder if we will be the first generation in American history to leave our children with fewer opportunities and a less prosperous nation than the one we inherited.', 66572, 0), (459298, 'I''m not one of those who wants to purge our society of our Christian history.', 1716, 0), (459299, 'We made history when President Obama appointed Sonia Sotomayor, a proud Latina, the first Hispanic Supreme Court justice. And as the President likes to say, ''Every single one of them wasn''t just the best Latino for the job, but the best person for the job.''', 73055, 0), (459300, 'I am totally fascinated by people and our history as I understand and continue to explore it. People have so much to give and so far to go and yet we have given and gone a great distance. It''s really just interesting to ask: why not? And see where that takes me.', 491, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459301, 'The process of making natural history films is to try to prevent the animal knowing you are there, so you get glimpses of a non-human world, and that is a transporting thing.', 3969, 0), (459302, 'The lesson of history is that you do not get a sustained economic recovery as long as the financial system is in crisis.', 66590, 0), (459303, 'I know that many of you do wear such a cross of Christ, not in any ostentatious way, not in a way that might harm you at your work or recreation, but a simple indication that you value the role of Jesus Christ in the history of the world, that you are trying to live by Christ''s standards in your own daily life.', 67235, 0), (459304, 'What would be the nicest thing I could say about Newt Gingrich? He may be one of the great supporters of the humanities, because you have people who don''t want to study the social sciences, because it''s not profitable, and now Newt, as the highest-paid historian in American history, may be an encouragement to people to study history.', 71472, 0), (459305, 'With copious evidence ranging from Plato''s haughtiness to Beethoven''s tirades, we may conclude that the most brilliant people of history tend to be a prickly lot.', 1195, 0), (459306, 'Optimists are usually wrong. But all the great change in history, positive change, was done by optimists.', 67869, 0), (459307, 'As nations we should also commit afresh to righting past wrongs. In Australia we began this recently with the first Australians - the oldest continuing culture in human history. On behalf of the Australian Parliament, this year I offered an apology to indigenous Australians for the wrongs they had suffered in the past.', 67684, 0), (459308, 'The message of Passover remains as powerful as ever. Freedom is won not on the battlefield but in the classroom and the home. Teach your children the history of freedom if you want them never to lose it.', 4059, 0), (459309, 'The hallmark of our times is change and acceleration, but we have to provide the history.', 66721, 0), (459310, 'The moment that changed me for ever was when I had my first seminar with my history professor at the University of Sussex. I realised that history would answer all the questions I had spent my life asking. It was an extraordinary moment.', 605, 0), (459311, 'I once won a second prize in a history concert. My parents came to the ceremony. Somebody else had won the prize for best all-around student. Afterwards my father said to me, ''Never, ever disgrace me like that again.'' When I tell my Western friends, they are aghast. But I adore my father. It didn''t knock my self-esteem at all.', 3273, 0), (459312, 'No back in the history of football was ever worth two fumbles a game.', 62953, 0), (459313, 'Open your refrigerator door, and you summon forth more light than the total amount enjoyed by most households in the 18th century. The world at night, for much of history, was a very dark place indeed.', 1068, 0), (459314, 'If we look at American history, between 1942 and 1947, the data that was collected by the Census Bureau was handed over to the FBI and other organizations at the request of President Roosevelt, and that''s how the Japanese were rounded up and put into the internment camps.', 66573, 0), (459315, 'The thing that interests me most about family history is the gap between the things we think we know about our families and the realities.', 73056, 0), (459316, 'I don''t think all buildings have to be iconic, but the history of the world has shown us that cultures build iconic buildings for their major public buildings.', 67568, 0), (459317, 'Elimination of illiteracy is as serious an issue to our history as the abolition of slavery.', 74, 0), (459318, 'Yes, the Bible should be taught in our schools because it is necessary to understand the Bible if we are to truly understand our own culture and how it came to be. The Bible has influenced every part of western culture from our art, music, and history, to our sense of fairness, charity, and business.', 3956, 0), (459319, 'Personally, my interests are ancient history and ancient civilizations. In my own life, I''d like to go to places like Easter Island.', 67437, 0), (459320, 'Captain Cook discovered Australia looking for the Terra Incognita. Christopher Columbus thought he was finding India but discovered America. History is full of events that happened because of an imaginary tale.', 736, 0), (459321, 'History is rich with adventurous men, long on charisma, with a highly developed instinct for their own interests, who have pursued personal power - bypassing parliaments and constitutions, distributing favours to their minions, and conflating their own desires with the interests of the community.', 736, 0), (459322, 'In the digital universe, our personal history and its sense of narrative is succeeded by our social networking profile - a snapshot of the current moment. The information itself - our social graph of friends and likes - is a product being sold to market researchers in order to better predict and guide our futures.', 13581, 0), (459323, 'People from different parts of the world can respond to the same story if it says something to them about their own history and their own experience.', 9773, 0), (459324, 'Men do not learn much from the lessons of history and that is the most important of all the lessons of history.', 1032, 0), (459325, 'I''ve always really, really wanted to go to Egypt and go inside some pyramids and just hang out there. I don''t know why. I don''t like hot weather, and I don''t like the desert, but something about the pyramid and the mummies and all their history there, I''d love to go check it out.', 72815, 0), (459326, 'Bulls don''t read. Bears read financial history. As markets fall to bits, the bears dust off the Dutch tulip mania of 1637, the Banque Royale of 1719-20, the railway speculation of the 1840s, the great crash of 1929.', 68800, 0), (459327, 'Black history isn''t a separate history. This is all of our history, this is American history, and we need to understand that. It has such an impact on kids and their values and how they view black people.', 73057, 0), (459328, 'History teaches us that men and nations behave wisely once they have exhausted all other alternatives.', 43480, 0), (459329, 'Mankind has probably done more damage to the Earth in the 20th century than in all of previous human history.', 21403, 0), (459330, 'Cameramen are among the most extraordinarily able and competent people I know. They have to have an insight into natural history that gives them a sixth sense of what the creature is going to do, so they can be ready to follow.', 3969, 0), (459331, 'Remember that in every single case in history the process of adaptation has been one of exceeding slowness. Do not look for the impossible, but do not let your path deviate from the quiet and steadfast insistence on full opportunities for your powers.', 67361, 0), (459332, 'I will come out with my interpretation. If I''m wrong, fine. It will become part of the debris of history, part of the give and take.', 40728, 0), (459333, 'For it is the duty of an astronomer to compose the history of the celestial motions through careful and expert study.', 4674, 0), (459334, 'From tea parties to the election in Massachusetts, we are witnessing the single greatest political pushback in American history.', 66707, 0), (459335, 'The people who have really made history are the martyrs.', 2200, 0), (459336, 'I never really had to put much thought into my race, and neither did anybody else. I knew I was black. I knew there was a history that accompanied my skin color, and my parents taught me to be proud of it. End of story.', 68399, 0), (459337, 'People that are really very weird can get into sensitive positions and have a tremendous impact on history.', 17186, 0), (459338, 'The reason I call myself a documentary photographer is the idea of how photographs contain and participate in history.', 72823, 0), (459339, 'If the Philippines must remain under the control of Spain, they will necessarily have to be transformed in a political sense, for the course of their history and the needs of their inhabitants so require.', 3961, 0), (459340, 'I know that we will be judged in history by not only how we disrupt terrorism but how we protect the civil liberties and constitutional rights of all Americans, even Americans who don''t wish us well. We must do all these things exceptionally well.', 68772, 0), (459341, 'We are fast approaching the stage of the ultimate inversion: the stage where the government is free to do anything it pleases, while the citizens may act only by permission; which is the stage of the darkest periods of human history, the stage of rule by brute force.', 631, 0), (459342, 'History is a relentless master. It has no present, only the past rushing into the future. To try to hold fast is to be swept aside.', 1680, 0), (459343, 'Never, never and never again shall it be that this beautiful land will again experience the oppression of one by another.', 1722, 0), (459344, 'Anyone who knows history, particularly the history of Europe, will, I think, recognize that the domination of education or of government by any one particular religious faith is never a happy arrangement for the people.', 141, 0), (459345, 'Sometimes history takes things into its own hands.', 14586, 0), (459346, 'The fall of the Berlin Wall makes for nice pictures. But it all started in the shipyards.', 63581, 0), (459347, 'In the course of American history, great steps are taken by ordinary people, and ordinary people are not perfect.', 10856, 0), (459348, 'There are still many causes worth sacrificing for, so much history yet to be made.', 1997, 0), (459349, 'President Obama is a gifted politician. He is gifted with rhetoric virtuosity. He is gifted with the ability to lie directly to camera without blinking. And he is gifted with some of the most incompetent conservative opposition in the history of the country.', 17797, 0), (459350, 'He who puts out his hand to stop the wheel of history will have his fingers crushed.', 63581, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459351, 'I think Hefner himself wants to go down in history as a person of sophistication and glamour. But the last person I would want to go down in history as is Hugh Hefner.', 1739, 0), (459352, 'If past history was all there was to the game, the richest people would be librarians.', 6410, 0), (459353, 'A lot of young players don''t really know much about the history of the game and a lot of them are missing out on what the game is all about, especially the whole concept of sportsmanship and teamwork.', 19298, 0), (459354, 'If given a chance, I would really want to explore the monuments in Delhi, like Qutub Minar and the forts. I have been there as a child, but now I want to go back and understand the history and significance behind them. We take all of these things for granted in life.', 71082, 0), (459355, 'The so-called ''materialistic conception of history,'' with the crude elements of genius of the early form which appeared, for instance, in the ''Communist Manifesto,'' still prevails only in the minds of laymen and dilettantes.', 11020, 0), (459356, 'There are no extraordinary men... just extraordinary circumstances that ordinary men are forced to deal with.', 68712, 0), (459357, 'The importance of the river cannot be overstated in the history of the country, or the development of the nation.', 73058, 0), (459358, 'History is a race between education and catastrophe.', 3173, 0), (459359, 'History offers us vicarious experience. It allows the youngest student to possess the ground equally with his elders; without a knowledge of history to give him a context for present events, he is at the mercy of every social misdiagnosis handed to him.', 6191, 0), (459360, 'History does not long entrust the care of freedom to the weak or the timid.', 2119, 0), (459361, 'Rome - the city of visible history, where the past of a whole hemisphere seems moving in funeral procession with strange ancestral images and trophies gathered from afar.', 215, 0), (459362, 'If the history of the Day of Atonement has anything to say to us now it is: never relieve individuals of moral responsibility. The more we have, the more we grow.', 4059, 0), (459363, 'You don''t change the course of history by turning the faces of portraits to the wall.', 8325, 0), (459364, 'History keeps her secrets longer than most of us. But she has one secret that I will reveal to you tonight in the greatest confidence. Sometimes there are no winners at all. And sometimes nobody needs to lose.', 5956, 0), (459365, 'Today, for the first time in history, a Bishop of Rome sets foot on English soil. This fair land, once a distant outpost of the pagan world, has become, through the preaching of the Gospel, a beloved and gifted portion of Christ''s vineyard.', 66871, 0), (459366, 'All in all, for someone who was immersed in, fascinated by, and dedicated to flight, I was disappointed by the wrinkle in history that had brought me along one generation late. I had missed all the great times and adventures in flight.', 2004, 0), (459367, 'History is full of examples of regimes that were oppressing at home and aggressive abroad, and I can''t think of too many liberal democracies engaging in counterfeiting, drug running, missile proliferation, and just about any other illegal activity you can think of as North Korea does.', 73059, 0), (459368, 'The travail of freedom and justice is not easy, but nothing serious and important in life is easy. The history of humanity has been a continuing struggle against temptation and tyranny - and very little worthwhile has ever been achieved without pain.', 60667, 0), (459369, 'The time is coming when the pressure of population on the means of subsistence will be felt here as it is now felt in Europe and Asia. Then will the world enter upon a new stage of its history - the final competition of races, for which the Anglo-Saxon is being schooled.', 73060, 0), (459370, 'Nowhere else in history has there ever been a flag that stands for the right to burn itself. This is the fractal of our flag. It stands for the right to destroy itself.', 1601, 0), (459371, 'We made them drink poison last night and Saddam Hussein''s soldiers and his great forces gave the Americans a lesson which will not be forgotten by history. Truly.', 73061, 0), (459372, 'A country grows in history not only because of the heroism of its troops on the field of battle, it grows also when it turns to justice and to right for the conservation of its interests.', 73062, 0), (459373, 'Never in our country''s history have we witnessed a natural disaster that has impacted so many people in such a wide area. In fact, as of the writing of this column, millions of people along the Gulf Coast have been displaced from their homes in a period of only five days.', 73063, 0), (459374, 'I go to the Natural History Museum and look at the cage of stuffed starlings there. But my favourite thing is the big blue whale. The scale of it is unbelievable, and makes you feel how insignificant you are as a human being.', 73064, 0), (459375, 'The history of free men is never really written by chance but by choice their choice!', 2119, 0), (459376, 'This is an exciting time. A new chapter in our history.', 17445, 0), (459377, 'History is full of examples of people who clamp down after they began to enjoy too much freedom. Freedom can lead to instability, anarchy, and confusion. So there can be a moral counter-revolution.', 68157, 0), (459378, 'I seldom go into a natural history museum without feeling as if I were attending a funeral.', 1069, 0), (459379, 'Recognizing Quebec as being different, recognizing our history, recognizing our identity, has never meant a weakening of Quebec and has never been a threat to national unity.', 73065, 0), (459380, 'To study history means submitting to chaos and nevertheless retaining faith in order and meaning.', 305, 0), (459381, 'I think you can learn from history.', 34704, 0), (459382, 'We are not merely passive pawns of historical forces nor are we victims of the past. We can shape and direct history.', 1750, 0), (459383, 'My inspiration is always love and history, and my passion to a fault is craftsmanship and responsibility. Those are the simplest things. It goes beyond jewelry. It''s every part of my life.', 73066, 0), (459384, 'My opinion is that politicians should be humble in the face of history. And whenever history is a matter of debate, it should be left in the hands of historians and experts.', 67426, 0), (459385, 'We have not invaded anyone. We have not conquered anyone. We have not grabbed their land, their culture, their history and tried to enforce our way of life on them.', 1798, 0), (459386, 'The voice of passion is better than the voice of reason. The passionless cannot change history.', 73067, 0), (459387, 'Do you really believe that the Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, plans to be a loser in history?', 19074, 0), (459388, 'We live in an era of globalization and the era of the woman. Never in the history of the world have women been more in control of their destiny.', 57450, 0), (459389, 'All the things that are part of your heritage make you British - that makes this country what it is. It''s part of your history. And here, unlike America, it''s still living history.', 1068, 0), (459390, 'If you go back far enough and get a wider enough picture of history, we have let go of many things that follow a religious narrative. We don''t burn witches anymore. Most people would consider that barbaric. We don''t sacrifice human beings, which was a religious act practiced by numerous cultures on this planet.', 10504, 0), (459391, 'Indeed, scientific truth by consensus has had a uniformly bad history.', 73068, 0), (459392, 'Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!', 17473, 0), (459393, 'We don''t want tradition. We want to live in the present and the only history that is worth a tinker''s dam is the history we make today.', 1796, 0), (459394, 'We used to root for the Indians against the cavalry, because we didn''t think it was fair in the history books that when the cavalry won it was a great victory, and when the Indians won it was a massacre.', 39403, 0), (459395, 'When the rich think about the poor, they have poor ideas.', 71187, 0), (459396, 'I love doing normal things - movies, shopping, going out with friends, writing, reading, taking hot bubble baths - that''s a big one for relaxation. I also love to go to art and history museums.', 11155, 0), (459397, 'Black History Month must be more than just a month of remembrance it should be a tribute to our history and reminder of the work that lies in the months and years ahead.', 70606, 0), (459398, 'If some peoples pretend that history or geography gives them the right to subjugate other races, nations, or peoples, there can be no peace.', 9998, 0), (459399, 'Oh, do not read history, for that I know must be false.', 66825, 0), (459400, 'I''m sure that was the right step, even though, formally speaking, it may seem disadvantageous for a president to resign. But, looking into what is happening today and what is going to happen in the future, I think history will show I made the right decision.', 73069, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459401, 'If you think you have it tough, read history books.', 2460, 0), (459402, 'Now, when I hear that Christians are getting together in order to defend the people of Israel, of course it brings joy to my heart. And it simply says, look, people have learned from history.', 10, 0), (459403, 'Street League Skateboarding is the premier professional skateboarding league in the world, with the biggest prize money in history.', 73070, 0), (459404, 'I''m focused on being the best, making history.', 69308, 0), (459405, 'I''m truly worried about the country''s direction. I can tell you this categorically, we''ve got the weakest president and the weakest governor in the history of my 50 years of public service.', 73071, 0), (459406, 'Throughout American history many of our social gains and much of our progress toward democracy were made possible by the active intervention of the federal government.', 66756, 0), (459407, 'I subscribe to William Faulkner''s'' view that history is not just about what we were before but who we are now.', 10198, 0), (459408, 'What is history? An echo of the past in the future a reflex from the future on the past.', 98, 0), (459409, 'The history of mankind is the instant between two strides taken by a traveler.', 629, 0), (459410, 'The Chinese government wants me to say that for many centuries Tibet has been part of China. Even if I make that statement, many people would just laugh. And my statement will not change past history. History is history.', 5025, 0), (459411, 'There''s something quite exciting when you have a history with somebody and you see them do new and different things.', 792, 0), (459412, 'Literature overtakes history, for literature gives you more than one life. It expands experience and opens new opportunities to readers.', 3377, 0), (459413, 'There are constant cycles in history. There is loss, but it is always followed by regeneration. The tales of our elders who remember such cycles are very important to us now.', 21155, 0), (459414, 'Hold those things that tell your history and protect them. During slavery, who was able to read or write or keep anything? The ability to have somebody to tell your story to is so important. It says: ''I was here. I may be sold tomorrow. But you know I was here.''', 74, 0), (459415, 'The whole westward expansion myth is seen as romantic. But it''s a joke, a blot on American history.', 73072, 0), (459416, 'Time is my greatest enemy.', 71187, 0), (459417, 'Outside the kingdom of the Lord there is no nation which is greater than any other. God and history will remember your judgment.', 15968, 0), (459418, 'I would put our legislative and foreign policy accomplishments in our first two years against any president - with the possible exceptions of Johnson, FDR, and Lincoln - just in terms of what we''ve gotten done in modern history. But, you know, but when it comes to the economy, we''ve got a lot more work to do. And we''re gonna keep on at it.', 1693, 0), (459419, 'What I love about the stories of the Great Migration is that this is not ancient history; this is living history. Most people of color can find someone in their own family who had experienced a migration of some kind, knowing the sense of dislocation, longing and fortitude.', 12183, 0), (459420, 'Civilization is a movement and not a condition, a voyage and not a harbor.', 63443, 0), (459421, 'Beware of endeavoring to become a great man in a hurry. One such attempt in ten thousand may succeed. These are fearful odds.', 1827, 0), (459422, 'It''s a very good historical book about history.', 17186, 0), (459423, 'In my view, far from deserving condemnation for their courageous reporting, the New York Times, the Washington Post and other newspapers should be commended for serving the purpose that the Founding Fathers saw so clearly.', 69807, 0), (459424, 'What Britain needs is an iron lady.', 1945, 0), (459425, 'Here men from the planet Earth first set foot upon the Moon. July 1969 AD. We came in peace for all mankind.', 2004, 0), (459426, 'I do not think it is an exaggeration to say history is largely a history of inflation, usually inflations engineered by governments for the gain of governments.', 70199, 0), (459427, 'I think the Lewis and Clark Expedition was the greatest undertaking in American History. I think landing a man on the moon pales next to it.', 7949, 0), (459428, 'To take wine into our mouths is to savor a droplet of the river of human history.', 8863, 0), (459429, 'But every historical statement and legitimization itself moves within a certain relation to history.', 2500, 0), (459430, 'The history of saints is mainly the history of insane people.', 2005, 0), (459431, 'You know, I think the, the crucial thing, you know, we have put in place what is, is just simply the biggest, boldest recovery package in history, right; the stimulus package, biggest ever; the financial rescue, absolutely comprehensive; a housing plan - that is incredible medicine for the economy. And we fully expect it to work.', 71517, 0), (459432, 'I''m very comfortable with where history will judge me.', 73073, 0), (459433, 'The Gospel is not a theory the Gospel is not a philosophy or an idea the Gospel is not a way of thinking or feeling. The Gospel is an event in history.', 1395, 0), (459434, 'I think my attitudes about the past are very traditional. You can''t ignore history; you can''t escape it even if you want to. You might as well know where you come from, and you might as well know that everything has been done in some shape or form.', 67568, 0), (459435, 'The American people need to know that there are folks here fighting as hard as they can for individual liberty, economic freedom, appropriate national security and the fundamental moral values that have made our nation the greatest nation in the history of mankind.', 73074, 0), (459436, 'I was brought up to understand Darwin''s theory of evolution. I spent hours and hours in the Natural History Museum in London looking at the descriptions of how different kinds of animals had evolved, looking at the sequence of fossil bones looking gradually more and more and more and more like the modern fossil.', 2086, 0), (459437, 'I actively pursue experiences that are unlike any others that I''ve experienced and cultures that I don''t know and unfamiliar places and unfamiliar history and things like that.', 11629, 0), (459438, 'I went into boxing, and I''m bisexual, and I still achieved and performed at the highest level, and I came away with gold and made history, so with that said, anything is possible.', 73075, 0), (459439, 'You can''t change history. These things happened the way they did. What you can change is how you look at it and how you understand that it takes the good moments and it takes the difficult moments to move forward.', 13808, 0), (459440, 'I am responsible only to God and history.', 73076, 0), (459441, 'The majority see the obstacles; the few see the objectives; history records the successes of the latter, while oblivion is the reward of the former.', 877, 0), (459442, 'The life history of the individual is first and foremost an accommodation to the patterns and standards traditionally handed down in his community.', 9314, 0), (459443, 'For the first time in the history of mankind, one generation literally has the power to destroy the past, the present and the future, the power to bring time to an end.', 15498, 0), (459444, 'One truth stands firm. All that happens in world history rests on something spiritual. If the spiritual is strong, it creates world history. If it is weak, it suffers world history.', 1006, 0), (459445, 'For the very first time the young are seeing history being made before it is censored by their elders.', 992, 0), (459446, 'The writer may very well serve a movement of history as its mouthpiece, but he cannot of course create it.', 1336, 0), (459447, 'Seventy years ago this November, Vladimir Lenin created the modern totalitarian state, transforming simpler forms of tyranny into history''s most sophisticated apparatus of rule by terror.', 73077, 0), (459448, 'You have reckoned that history ought to judge the past and to instruct the contemporary world as to the future. The present attempt does not yield to that high office. It will merely tell how it really was.', 73078, 0), (459449, 'History provides neither compensation for suffering nor penalties for wrong.', 73079, 0), (459450, 'The Iraqi Free Press, which did not exist 18 months ago because there was no such thing as the Iraqi Free Press, broke a story about the U.N. Oil-for-Food scandal, which could potentially turn out to be the largest scandal in history.', 66641, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459451, 'You know that''s history, that''s why some people say that my stuff is retro, but I don''t agree.', 69189, 0), (459452, 'According to the scientific naturalist version of cosmic history, nature is a permanently closed system of material effects that can never be influenced by something from outside - like God, for example.', 13694, 0), (459453, 'If I don''t tell it all now, the story in the history books will always be imperfect and that would be wrong.', 73080, 0), (459454, 'To those of you who study history, economics, sociology, literature and language I present the challenge of the utilization of the enormous resources in our grasp to the problem of creating a genuinely good life for yourselves and your children.', 70828, 0), (459455, 'Yeah, I read history. But it doesn''t make you nice. Hitler read history, too.', 17330, 0), (459456, 'In this world without quiet corners, there can be no easy escapes from history, from hullabaloo, from terrible, unquiet fuss.', 2065, 0), (459457, 'Every major question in history is a religious question. It has more effect in molding life than nationalism or a common language.', 4439, 0), (459458, 'I set my sights upon becoming the kind of artist who would make a contribution to art history.', 69869, 0), (459459, 'This above all makes history useful and desirable it unfolds before our eyes a glorious record of exemplary actions.', 14801, 0), (459460, 'Throughout human history, the apostles of purity, those who have claimed to possess a total explanation, have wrought havoc among mere mixed-up human beings.', 2065, 0), (459461, 'There never has been a time in our history when work was so abundant or when wages were as high, whether measured by the currency in which they are paid or by their power to supply the necessaries and comforts of life.', 45276, 0), (459462, 'You look at the greatest villains in human history, the fascists, the autocrats, they all wanted people to kneel before them because they don''t love themselves enough.', 1101, 0), (459463, 'Any good broadcast, not just an Olympic broadcast, should have texture to it. It should have information, should have some history, should have something that''s offbeat, quirky, humorous, and where called for it, should have journalism, and judiciously it should also have commentary. That''s my ideal.', 73081, 0), (459464, 'What has made America amazing has been the fact that throughout our history, throughout the more than 200 years of our history, there have been men and women of courage who stood up and decided it was more important to look out for the future of their children and their grandchildren than their own political futures.', 73082, 0), (459465, 'So many struggled so that all of us could have a voice in this great democracy and live up to the first three words of our constitution: We the people. I love that phrase so much. Throughout our country''s history, we''ve expanded the meaning of that phrase to include more and more of us. That''s what it means to move forward.', 37611, 0), (459466, 'September 11 was terrible but, if one goes back over the history of the IRA, what happened to the Americans wasn''t that terrible.', 217, 0), (459467, 'What does the artist do? He draws connections. He ties the invisible threads between things. He dives into history, be it the history of mankind, the geological history of the Earth or the beginning and end of the manifest cosmos.', 73083, 0), (459468, 'In most organizations, change comes in only two flavors: trivial and traumatic. Review the history of the average organization and you''ll discover long periods of incremental fiddling punctuated by occasional bouts of frantic, crisis-driven change.', 30035, 0), (459469, 'If students get a sound education in the history, social effects and psychological biases of technology, they may grow to be adults who use technology rather than be used by it.', 3741, 0), (459470, 'Life, it is true, can be grasped in all its confused futility merely by opening one''s eyes and sitting passively, a spectator on the stands of history - but to understand the social processes and conflicts, the interplay between individual and group, even the physicality of human experience, we have need of small-scale models.', 1747, 0), (459471, 'In the history of mankind there are recorded two great Inversions. The first, set forth by the Nazarene to the effect that love is a greater power and more real than vengeance. The second proclaimed the earth to be a sphere revolving in its course around the sun. These affirmations were made in the face of all evidence sacred to the contrary.', 52631, 0), (459472, 'When I saw that Wrestlemania had broken an indoor attendance record, I just walked into a wrestling office, Championship Wrestling in Florida, during the offseason, and they introduced me to Hiro Matsuda, who became my mentor... and the rest is history!', 67532, 0), (459473, 'The naturalist worldview is a good way to feel grounded and feel part of something that isn''t based on fairy tales. It''s based on observable facts in the human and in the biological history of the planet. I think that can be a source for comfort.', 10504, 0), (459474, 'In the 7th grade, I made a 20-foot long mural of the Lewis and Clark Trail while we were studying that in history because I knew I wasn''t going to be able to spit back the names and the dates and all that stuff on a test.', 10106, 0), (459475, 'History is moving the furniture around in the house of mankind just about everywhere but the U.S.A. Things have changed, except here, where people come and go through the rooms of state, and everything looks shabbier by the day, and lethargy eats away at the upholstery like an acid fog, and the walls reverberate with meaningless oratory.', 14299, 0), (459476, 'The history of American agriculture suggests that you can have transformation without a master plan, without knowing all the answers up front.', 13590, 0), (459477, 'No period of history has ever been great or ever can be that does not act on some sort of high, idealistic motives, and idealism in our time has been shoved aside, and we are paying the penalty for it.', 2606, 0), (459478, 'People who make history know nothing about history. You can see that in the sort of history they make.', 67663, 0), (459479, 'If you review the commercial history, you will discover anyone who controls oriental trade will get hold of global wealth.', 73084, 0), (459480, 'But today, government is taking those rights from us, pretending that it gives us our rights. Indeed, those rights come from God, and it was recognized throughout our history as such.', 66757, 0), (459481, 'History shows how feeble are barriers of paper.', 4502, 0), (459482, 'OUR history begins before we are born. We represent the hereditary influences of our race, and our ancestors virtually live in us.', 73085, 0), (459483, 'You should read history and look at ostracism, persecution, martyrdom, and that kind of thing. They always happen to the best men, you know.', 215, 0), (459484, 'I had a go at changing history - maybe not all by myself - I fought at the battle of Normandy, I slogged through the Ardennes, and I celebrated the liberation of Paris on the streets with beautiful French girls throwing flowers at me. I said good-bye to my first true love and discovered what I really wanted to do with my life.', 73086, 0), (459485, 'You can''t say history teaches us this or that; it gives us more questions than answers, and many answers to every question.', 6144, 0), (459486, 'The past actually happened but history is only what someone wrote down.', 2262, 0), (459487, 'A truly American sentiment recognizes the dignity of labor and the fact that honor lies in honest toil.', 18162, 0), (459488, 'It was a Greek tragedy. Nixon was fulfilling his own nature. Once it started it could not end otherwise.', 2393, 0), (459489, 'The judicial system is the most expensive machine ever invented for finding out what happened and what to do about it.', 73087, 0), (459490, 'France, and the whole of Europe have a great culture and an amazing history. Most important thing though is that people there know how to live! In America they''ve forgotten all about it. I''m afraid that the American culture is a disaster.', 148, 0), (459491, 'History is an endless repetition of the wrong way of living.', 6034, 0), (459492, 'God cannot alter the past, though historians can.', 4111, 0), (459493, 'Most of us spend too much time on the last twenty-four hours and too little on the last six thousand years.', 1167, 0), (459494, 'Why should we honour those that die upon the field of battle? A man may show as reckless a courage in entering into the abyss of himself.', 62867, 0), (459495, 'France is delighted at this new opportunity to show the world that when one has the will one can succeed in joining peoples who have been brought close by history.', 2885, 0), (459496, 'On the day when man told the story of his life to man, history was born.', 7208, 0), (459497, 'In the Confederate Army, an officer was judged by stark courage alone, and this made it possible for the Confederacy to live four years.', 69806, 0), (459498, 'From the beginning of our history the country has been afflicted with compromise. It is by compromise that human rights have been abandoned.', 63645, 0), (459499, 'God created us for love, for union, for forgiveness and compassion and, yet, that has not been our storyline. That has not been our history.', 3970, 0), (459500, 'When great changes occur in history, when great principles are involved, as a rule the majority are wrong.', 10499, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (459501, 'There is at least one point in the history of any company when you have to change dramatically to rise to the next level of performance. Miss that moment - and you start to decline.', 68837, 0), (459502, 'After Jackie Robinson the most important black in baseball history is Reggie Jackson, I really mean that.', 65245, 0), (459503, 'The greatest untapped reservoir of raw material in the history of our game is the black race.', 62664, 0), (459504, 'We stand a chance of getting a president who has probably killed more people before he gets into office than any president in the history of the United States.', 5975, 0), (459505, 'May it not be that, just as we have to have faith in Him, God has to have faith in us and, considering the history of the human race so far, may it not be that ''faith'' is even more difficult for Him than it is for us?', 219, 0), (459506, 'For my part, I consider that it will be found much better by all parties to leave the past to history, especially as I propose to write that history myself.', 3621, 0), (459507, 'Politics can be relatively fair in the breathing spaces of history; at its critical turning points there is no other rule possible than the old one, that the end justifies the means.', 14934, 0), (459508, 'My friends, history, history calls us to this time and to this place. A solemn choice rests with us - where do we go from here? Do we move slowly and incrementally? Or do we seize the challenge of our time and tackle the great issues of our day.', 73088, 0), (459509, 'Since the dawn of time, traditional marriage - the union between one man and one woman - has been the building block of civilization, and at no point in our nation''s history has that foundation been under more severe attack than now.', 68351, 0), (459510, 'The state can be and has often been in the course of history the main source of mischief and disaster.', 9998, 0), (459511, 'There are two kinds of man: the ones who make history and the ones who endure it.', 51440, 0), (459512, 'No doubt one may quote history to support any cause, as the devil quotes scripture.', 3040, 0), (459513, 'But you have to understand, my beard is so nasty. I mean, it''s the only beard in the history of Western civilization that makes Bob Dylan''s beard look good.', 47735, 0), (459514, 'History seems to be so clumsy.', 50409, 0), (459515, 'What I am is a thinking, feeling human being compelled by history.', 73089, 0), (459516, 'I call on everyone of goodwill both in Ireland and abroad to join now in ensuring that the beginning of peace becomes a reality, before this year is out. Let us together open a new era in our history.', 73090, 0), (459517, 'The broadest pattern of history - namely, the differences between human societies on different continents - seems to me to be attributable to differences among continental environments, and not to biological differences among peoples themselves.', 7867, 0), (459518, 'I would consider all of the legislation which I have supported meaningless if I were to sit idly by, silent, during a period which may go down in history as an era when we permitted the curtailment of our liberties.', 68777, 0), (459519, 'When history looks back, it will prove what I''ll die knowing.', 7905, 0), (459520, 'We are looking for targets that have a tremendous strategic fit for the company. The colleges must have complementary education programs, have an excellent reputation, long operating history and solid regulatory compliance.', 73091, 0), (459521, 'At many points during our nation''s history, there have been times - known in our history textbooks as ''panics'' - when adverse conditions affecting the financial and economic sectors of the country have caused individuals to hoard more than they need.', 73063, 0), (459522, 'Yes, we''ve seen it all before. And yes, those who do not study history are condemned to repeat it. But no, the sky is not falling - baseball is