 of the 1960s.', 1920, 0), (459613, 'Strip malls are history.', 22320, 0), (459614, 'What''s it like to envision the ten-thousand-year environmental impact of tossing a plastic bottle into the trash bin, all in the single second it takes to actually toss it? Or the ten-thousand-year history of the fossil fuel being burned to drive to work or iron a shirt? It may be environmentally progressive, but it''s not altogether pleasant.', 13581, 0), (459615, 'In Jewish history there are no coincidences.', 10, 0), (459616, 'I can see clearly now... that I was wrong in not acting more decisively and more forthrightly in dealing with Watergate.', 9695, 0), (459617, 'I let the American people down.', 9695, 0), (459618, 'Life isn''t meant to be easy. It''s hard to take being on the top - or on the bottom. I guess I''m something of a fatalist. You have to have a sense of history, I think, to survive some of these things... Life is one crisis after another.', 9695, 0), (459619, 'I love studying Ancient History and seeing how empires rise and fall, sowing the seeds of their own destruction.', 21702, 0), (459620, 'The Russians feared Ike. They didn''t fear me.', 1763, 0), (459621, 'The Marine Corps is the Navy''s police force and as long as I am President that is what it will remain. They have a propaganda machine that is almost equal to Stalin''s.', 16121, 0), (459622, 'I realise that I do not change the course of history. I am an actor, I do a movie, that''s the end of it. You have to realise we are just clowns for hire. After I had success it was great, at first, not to worry about money. It was on my mind when I was growing up.', 68700, 0), (459623, 'It is the soothing thing about history that it does repeat itself.', 1267, 0), (459624, '90 percent of my time is spent on 10 percent of the world.', 1749, 0), (459625, 'September 11th was a moment when America had the sympathy of the world.', 7980, 0), (459626, 'Democratic nations must try to find ways to starve the terrorist and the hijacker of the oxygen of publicity on which they depend.', 1945, 0), (459627, 'I''m the only person of distinction who has ever had a depression named for him.', 7777, 0), (459628, 'Over the years, more than one reviewer has described my fantasy series, ''A Song of Ice and Fire'', as historical fiction about history that never happened, flavoured with a dash of sorcery and spiced with dragons. I take that as a compliment.', 169, 0), (459629, 'Imagination is always the fabric of social life and the dynamic of history. The influence of real needs and compulsions, of real interests and materials, is indirect because the crowd is never conscious of it.', 1662, 0), (459630, 'Let Indian history be set side by side with Europe history with what there is of the latter century by century and let us see whether India need blush at the comparison.', 4208, 0), (459631, 'History develops, art stands still.', 102, 0), (459632, 'The Arctic is a place that historically, during all preceding human history, has largely been an icy realm with an impact on ocean currents. That, in turn, influences the temperature of the planet. The Arctic is now vulnerable because of the excess carbon dioxide in the atmosphere, with a rate of melting that is stunning.', 67053, 0), (459633, 'Every library should try to be complete on something, if it were only the history of pinheads.', 24754, 0), (459634, 'You that would judge me, do not judge alone this book or that, come to this hallowed place where my friends'' portraits hang and look thereon; Ireland''s history in their lineaments trace; think where man''s glory most begins and ends and say my glory was I had such friends.', 62867, 0), (459635, 'I don''t know the history of my sport. I''m not like those people who know everything.', 56473, 0), (459636, 'I want to know why I''m alive. I want to understand. It''s like exploration; it''s like someone being interested in a place and its history, digging into the earth and looking for it, searching -