ith a drawerful of amazing jewelry. I don''t even have my ears pierced! But I have one bracelet that never comes off my wrist.', 70818, 0), (459939, 'Propaganda is amazing. People can be led to believe anything.', 753, 0), (459940, 'I don''t see the desert as barren at all; I see it as full and ripe. It doesn''t need to be flattered with rain. It certainly needs rain, but it does with what it has, and creates amazing beauty.', 7613, 0), (459941, 'Working with amazing people, you continue to learn and develop yourself, as an actor and as a person.', 69760, 0), (459942, 'Ever consider what pets must think of us? I mean, here we come back from a grocery store with the most amazing haul - chicken, pork, half a cow. They must think we''re the greatest hunters on earth!', 658, 0), (459943, 'Tell me, why is the media here so negative? Why are we in India so embarrassed to recognise our own strengths, our achievements? We are such a great nation. We have so many amazing success stories but we refuse to acknowledge them. Why?', 1798, 0), (459944, 'You get moments all the time that kind of make you pinch yourself, some of them make you quite emotional. Winning a BRIT was a big moment because we were just so excited to be at the awards in the first place. Selling out Madison Square Garden was pretty amazing too. Then we woke to the news that our UK tour was sold out. It was crazy.', 500, 0), (459945, 'The real art is not to come up with extraordinary clever words but to make ordinary simple words do extraordinary things. To use the language that we all use and to make amazing things occur.', 10147, 0), (459946, 'There''s nothing more confirming in your life than looking in front of you and seeing some really amazing people who you care a lot about who care a lot about you.', 73154, 0), (459947, 'I''m an amazing mama''s boy.', 9137, 0), (459948, 'When you look at the calculation, it''s amazing that every time you try to prove or disprove time travel, you''ve pushed Einstein''s 