th them is a pleasure for me.', 71313, 0), (459985, 'It''s amazing how confused and distracted and misdirected so many people are.', 10390, 0), (459986, 'The Southbank Centre Unlimited Festival was a distinct moment in time, an amazing counterpoint to the London 2012 Paralympics. There is no question that a major shift in perspective is taking place, that the world is waking up and greeting - as if for the first time - the extraordinary community of people with disability.', 69493, 0), (459987, 'My father is an amazing person. While he was a huge star, he never carried his stardom home and always remained simple and just our father at home. I have four siblings, and we were all very grounded. We lived a very simple life: would go in an auto rickshaw to school, played with normal boys.', 68920, 0), (459988, 'Nothing is more generally known than our duties which belong to Christianity; and yet, how amazing is it, nothing is less practiced?', 46036, 0), (459989, 'The video game culture was an important thing to keep alive in the film because we''re in a new era right now. The idea that kids can play video games like Grand Theft Auto or any video game is amazing. The video games are one step before a whole other virtual universe.', 68102, 0), (459990, 'Why is Cloud 9 so amazing? What is wrong with Cloud 8? That joke came off the top of my head, and the top of my head ain''t funny!', 27687, 0), (459991, 'I am fully committed to Hannah Montana. It''s what gave me this amazing opportunity to reach out to so many people. I''m really excited about our new season. We are making great new episodes that I can''t wait for our fans to see and I''m looking forward to the ''Hannah Montana'' movie that will be out in the spring.', 682, 0), (459992, 'Trophies and medals have never meant much to me. I''ve had amazing experiences, which let you feel like you''ve accomplished something.', 68268, 0), (459993, 'Texas women have an amazing sense of purpose when they lose it. They''re the b